---
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
import DocsSubnav from '../../../../components/DocsSubnav.astro';
import MythicDivider from '../../../../components/MythicDivider.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Recipe · Recurring agent on a schedule"
  description="Drop a YAML in .zana/scheduler/, reload, trigger. The agent runs detached on the daemon."
>
  <DocsSubnav />

  <section class="container-zana py-16">
    <p class="text-sm text-moss">
      <a href="/docs/recipes/" class="hover:text-forest">← All recipes</a>
    </p>
    <p class="ornament mt-4 text-xs text-gold">— scheduled agent —</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-5xl text-forest md:text-6xl">Recurring agent on a schedule.</h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg text-moss leading-relaxed">
      One YAML schema, two execution paths. The daemon path supports
      <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">cron</code> and full
      profile features; the <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">/loop</code>
      path is daemon-free and runs in a Claude Code session. <strong>Same file,
      same fields.</strong>
    </p>

    <article class="prose-zana mt-12 max-w-prose space-y-10">
      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest">1. Define the schedule</h2>
        <CodeBlock caption=".zana/scheduler/qa-spawn.yml" lang="yaml">{`id: qa-spawn
name: QA spawn-agent schedule
enabled: true
schedule:
  every: 24h          # or 5m, 1h, 2d — or cron: "0 2 * * *" (daemon-only)
action:
  type: spawn-agent
  profileId: researcher
  prompt: "Reply with the single word: PONG"
history:
  enabled: true
  retain: 5`}</CodeBlock>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest">2. Reload + trigger</h2>
        <CodeBlock caption="claude code · MCP" lang="text">{`zana_schedule_reload({})
// → { started: 1, skipped: 0, total: 1 }

zana_schedule_trigger({ scheduleId: "qa-spawn" })
// → { ok: true, result: { status: "success", agentId, finalStatus: "pending" } }

// poll until terminated
zana_list_agents({})
zana_agent_result({ agentId })
// → { completed: true, state: "terminated", result: "PONG" }`}</CodeBlock>
        <p class="mt-3 text-moss">
          Notice that <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">trigger</code> returns
          immediately — the agent runs detached on the daemon. Poll for the result, or wait for
          the schedule's history file to land it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest">Daemon vs <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">/loop</code> — which path?</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-forest/15">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead class="bg-parchment/60 text-forest">
              <tr>
                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold">Use the daemon when</th>
                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold">Use <code class="rounded bg-cream px-1 py-0.5">/loop</code> when</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-moss">
              <tr class="border-t border-forest/10">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top">You need <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1 py-0.5">cron</code> expressions</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top">In-session ad-hoc work — no daemon to run</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-forest/10">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top">Schedules must survive Claude Code restarts</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top">Prototyping — quick to start, quick to kill</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-forest/10">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top">Multiple workspaces sharing one daemon</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top">One workspace, one session, no extra processes</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-forest/10">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top">Full profile features (skills, tools, hooks)</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top">Lightweight: <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1 py-0.5">every: …</code> intervals only</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-moss"><code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">/zana:loop:start</code> refuses cron schedules and points you to the daemon path — it's a hard gate.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest">Drive it from <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">/loop</code></h2>
        <CodeBlock caption="claude code · zana-loop commands" lang="text">{`/zana:loop:define              # walk through authoring a new yml
/zana:loop:start               # pick a schedule (or 'all enabled') and arm a /loop
/zana:loop:start <scheduleId>  # arm one specific schedule
/zana:loop:stop                # kill all zana loops in this session
/zana:loop:stop <scheduleId>   # kill one specific loop`}</CodeBlock>
        <p class="mt-3 text-moss">Each loop is identified by a sentinel of the form <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">AGENT_LOOP_TICK_zana_&lt;id&gt;</code>.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest">Live test</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-moss">
          The daemon path is asserted by
          <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">scripts/qa/run-scheduler-agent-live.sh</code>
          — 4/4 passing against real Claude.
        </p>
      </section>

      <MythicDivider />

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest">Next</h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-moss">
          <li>· <a href="/docs/recipes/autopilot/" class="text-forest hover:text-berry">Goal-driven autopilot</a> — schedule a goal-driven loop instead of a single spawn.</li>
          <li>· <a href="/docs/cli/" class="text-forest hover:text-berry">CLI reference</a> — <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">zana schedule …</code> from the terminal.</li>
          <li>· <a href="https://github.com/grebmann1/zana/blob/main/docs/RECIPES.md#schedules" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-forest hover:text-berry">Full schedule recipe in RECIPES.md</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
